properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 10 at 12:38AM MST until February 10 at 6:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 6 AM MST early this morning.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with occasional gusts up to
65 mph.

* WHERE...Northern Snowy Range Foothills, including Elk Mountain
and Arlington.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM MST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. There will be a blow over
risk for lightweight, high profile vehicles including camping
and tractor trailers. In addition, patchy blowing snow may
result in brief periods of lower visibility.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM MST EARLY THIS MORNING
